## Agent Swarm — Native OIDC configuration
##
## Mode 2: Native OIDC middleware (PROPOSED — not yet implemented)
##
## These environment variables are the proposed interface for the native OIDC
## middleware (src/http/oidc.ts). They do NOT currently exist in the codebase.
## Add them to your .env file once native OIDC is shipped.
##
## Track progress: https://linear.app/desplega/issue/DES-445
##
## For SSO today, use Mode 1 (oauth2-proxy) or Mode 3 (trusted-header).
## See docs/guides/self-hosted-sso for the full guide.

# ── OIDC Provider ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Your IdP's OIDC discovery endpoint (RFC 8414).
#
#   Okta:     https://your-org.okta.com
#   Azure AD: https://login.microsoftonline.com/YOUR_TENANT_ID/v2.0
#   Google:   https://accounts.google.com
#   Keycloak: http://keycloak:8080/realms/YOUR_REALM
OIDC_ISSUER_URL=https://YOUR_IDP.example.com

OIDC_CLIENT_ID=YOUR_CLIENT_ID
OIDC_CLIENT_SECRET=YOUR_CLIENT_SECRET

# Must match the redirect URI registered in your IdP application.
OIDC_REDIRECT_URI=https://YOUR_SWARM_HOST/api/auth/oidc/callback

# Scopes to request. Include "groups" if your IdP exposes a groups claim
# and you want to use OIDC_GROUP_ROLE_MAP.
OIDC_SCOPES=openid email profile groups

# ── Group claim ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The JWT claim that contains the user's group memberships.
# Varies by provider:
#   Okta:      groups  (must be explicitly enabled in Okta app settings)
#   Azure AD:  roles   (v2 tokens; configure in App Registration > Token configuration)
#   Keycloak:  groups  (default; add a "groups" mapper to the client)
#   Google:    n/a     (groups require Admin SDK — standard OIDC only has profile/email)
OIDC_GROUP_CLAIM=groups

# ── Group → Role mapping ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Map IdP group names to swarm role names (JSON object).
#
# REQUIRES RBAC (DES-445) to be enabled — roles must exist before mapping.
# Without RBAC, this value is ignored even when native OIDC is implemented.
#
# Example:
#   engineering → member (can submit tasks, read own agent output)
#   admins      → admin  (full access)
#   read-only   → viewer (read-only dashboard access)
OIDC_GROUP_ROLE_MAP={"engineering":"member","admins":"admin","read-only":"viewer"}

# ── Trusted-header mode (Mode 3) ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
# When set, the API accepts this header as an authenticated identity.
# ONLY enable when all external traffic is routed through oauth2-proxy —
# never expose port 3013 directly to the internet when this is set.
#
# SSO_TRUSTED_HEADER=X-Forwarded-Email
